Columbia University, New York  ·  Sciences Po, Paris

A singular academic union between two of the world's most storied institutions — conferring two degrees, across two continents, in four years.

In the long history of elite higher education, certain combinations of institutions represent a rare convergence of prestige, rigour, and global reach. The Columbia–Sciences Po Dual BA is one such programme — a partnership between an Ivy League institution founded in 1754, and the grande école that has produced six French presidents and shaped global governance for over 150 years.

Columbia University — Morningside Heights, New York City. Founded 1754.
The Ivy League

Eight universities. Three centuries of shaping the world.

The Ivy League is an association of just eight universities in the United States — institutions whose names carry global weight in every field of human endeavour. They produce presidents, justices, Nobel laureates, and the architects of international institutions. Admission to any one of them is among the most competitive academic pursuits on earth.

The Weight of an Offer
Columbia University Acceptance Rate
3.7%
Second only to Harvard among all Ivy League institutions

Of every 100 students who apply to Columbia, fewer than 4 receive an offer. Columbia evaluates tens of thousands of applications from students who are, by any conventional measure, already exceptional — stellar academic records, outstanding test scores, and extraordinary achievement. And still, 96 out of every 100 are turned away.

What separates those who receive an offer is not simply the measurable. Columbia seeks something rarer and harder to quantify — the intangible qualities that no grade can capture.

📋
Stellar Academic Record
Years of consistent excellence across rigorous curricula. Columbia expects the highest standards — and still, grades alone are never enough.
🗣
Superb Interview Performance
The ability to articulate ideas with precision, intellectual confidence, and genuine curiosity — under pressure, in conversation with the world's best minds.
✍️
Outstanding Essays
The capacity to write with clarity, depth, and original voice. Essays reveal whether a student thinks independently — not whether they perform to expectation.
✨
The Intangible — Passion, Story & Singular Identity
More than any grade or score, Columbia seeks a person. A distinctive narrative. A depth of genuine passion. A quality of character and perspective that makes any room different when they enter it. This cannot be manufactured — it can only be found in those who are, in some essential way, already extraordinary.
Columbia University

Founded 1754. Still shaping the world.

Established by royal charter of King George II of Great Britain, Columbia is the fifth-oldest institution of higher learning in the United States. In its nearly three centuries of existence, it has educated men and women who altered the course of history — from the founders of the American republic, to the architects of the post-war international order, to Nobel laureates reshaping our understanding of the universe.

Sciences Po, Paris

Europe's most powerful school of political science — and the making of presidents.

Founded in 1872 in the heart of Paris, Sciences Po was established for a singular purpose: to train the leaders of nations. In the 150 years since, it has fulfilled this mandate with remarkable consistency. Sciences Po belongs to the grandes écoles — a small number of elite French institutions regarded as the training ground for the republic's ruling class, whose graduates populate the upper echelons of European and international institutions.

The Dual BA Programme

Two degrees. Two continents.
One extraordinary education.

The Columbia–Sciences Po Dual Bachelor of Arts is among the most distinctive undergraduate programmes available anywhere in the world. It is a full, joint academic partnership between two premier institutions, conferring upon its graduates a degree from each university. Students spend their first two years immersed in political science, economics, and international relations at Sciences Po in France — before completing their education at Columbia University in the heart of New York City.

Duration
4 years: 2 at Sciences Po (France) → 2 at Columbia (New York)
Degrees Conferred
Two separate diplomas: Columbia University BA + Sciences Po BA
Locations
Sciences Po regional campus, France → Columbia University, Manhattan
Selectivity
Among the most competitive international dual-degree programmes in existence
Field of Study
Social sciences, political science, international relations + Columbia major
Graduate Outcomes
Rhodes Scholars; alumni admitted to Harvard, Yale, Cambridge, Oxford graduate programmes

"Alumni of the Columbia–Sciences Po Dual BA include multiple Rhodes Scholars — among the most prestigious postgraduate fellowships in the world — and recent graduates have proceeded to the most selective graduate programmes globally, including Harvard, Yale, Cambridge, and Oxford."

— Programme Alumni Record

To receive an offer from this programme is to be recognised by two of the world's most distinguished institutions simultaneously — a distinction that places a candidate in genuinely rare international academic company.

The Significance of This Opportunity

What this offer represents

A conditional offer from the Columbia–Sciences Po Dual BA is recognition by two of the world's most distinguished institutions that a student possesses the intellectual calibre, character, and potential to join a programme of extraordinary selectivity.

Two Global Networks

Graduates enter both Columbia's 340,000-strong global network and Sciences Po's 55,000 alumni who populate the upper levels of international governance — a double advantage available to virtually no other undergraduate programme.

Two Degrees, Dual Credential

Upon graduation, the student holds credentials from both Columbia University and Sciences Po — a combination that signals, to any institution or employer worldwide, an uncommon breadth of international education and scholarly achievement.

Gateway to Harvard, Yale, Cambridge & Oxford

Alumni have proceeded to Harvard Law, Yale Law, Cambridge, Oxford, and comparable institutions at remarkable rates. The combination of a Columbia transcript and a Sciences Po education creates a graduate school application of uncommon distinction.

New York City — The World's Capital

Columbia's campus sits in Manhattan — the global centre of finance, law, media, and international affairs. The professional opportunities available to Columbia students in New York are unmatched by any other city on earth.

To be educated at Columbia and Sciences Po is to join a lineage of consequence.

The men and women who have passed through these institutions' gates have shaped constitutions, led nations, built international institutions, and advanced the frontiers of human knowledge. Barack Obama, Franklin and Theodore Roosevelt, and Ruth Bader Ginsburg at Columbia. Emmanuel Macron, François Hollande, and Pierre Trudeau at Sciences Po.

The opportunity to join that lineage is among the rarest a young scholar can receive.
